<H1>&nbsp;Chapter 15: </H1>
<blockquote>
  <h2><font size="6">Component Infrastructures:</font></h2>
</blockquote>
<p><font size="6">Placing Software Components in Context</font></p>

<h2>In the planning and design of component based system, we
can sometimes use questionnaires to help the designer
to focus on certain design issues.
An <a href="quest">example</a> shows the use
of a questionnaire to focus on design choices
for a remote voting system.
A <a href="questhealth">similar questionnaire</a>
is available for health care system design.
The <a href="http://people.cs.pitt.edu/~chang/163/c14/AK073a.htm">deployment and development diagrams for phone to phone system</a> and
the <a href="http://people.cs.pitt.edu/~chang/163/c14/AK073b.htm">deployment and development diagrams for phone to PC system</a> are illustrated.
</h2>

